                  rdfs:subClassOf mmoon:Case ,
                                  <http://purl.org/linguistics/gold/CaseProperty> ;
                  mmoon:definition """The casus rectus of a system is that case which marks the subject of a copula clause (or nominal clause). Thus, the nominative in the accusative system, the absolutive in the ergative system.

Phenomenology:
The casus rectus may be unmarked as against the oblique cases or may be based on a different declension stem.
[Christian Lehmann, under \"casus rectus\" at http://linguistik.uni-regensburg.de:8080/lido/Lido]"""@en ;
                  rdfs:label "Casus Rectus"@en .


