                    mmoon:externalDefinitionDesc """A causative verb is an n-place verb (with n > 1) which is derived from an n-1-place verb in such a way that the additional semantic slot is mapped onto the subject slot and is occupied by a superordinate agent which causes the situation designated by the base.

