                    rdfs:subClassOf mmoon:LinguisticCategory ;
                    mmoon:definition "Evidentiality expresses the source of information."@en ;
                    mmoon:example """Turkmen, for example, has four levels of evidentiality - direct, inferred, assumed, and reported. These are marked in the following way:

al-dy 's/he took';
al-ypdyr 's/he took (but I didn't see it)';
alan eken 's/he apparently took';
al-anmyş 'it is rumoured that s/he took'.

(http://www.glottopedia.org/index.php/Evidentiality)""" ;
                    mmoon:externalDefinition <http://purl.org/olia/olia-top.owl#EvidentialityFeature> ;
                    rdfs:label "Evidentiality"@en .


