                   rdfs:subClassOf mmoon:Word ,
                                   <http://www.w3.org/ns/lemon/ontolex#LexicalEntry> ;
                   mmoon:definition """A lexical entry is a word as it appears as an entry in a dictionary. It can be a lexeme or a grammatical word.
All lexical entries that inflect have a holistic abstract sense representing the core meaning shared by a set of closely-related word-forms. The lexical entry can be one of the word-forms which is chosen as the representative of the inflectional paradigm of the lexeme."""@en ;
                   rdfs:label "Lexical Entry"@en ;
                   <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#broadMatch> <http://purl.org/linguistics/gold/LexicalItem> .


###  http://mmoon.org/core/LinguisticCategory
mmoon:LinguisticCategory rdf:type owl:Class ;
