           owl:equivalentClass <http://purl.org/linguistics/gold/Stem> ;
           rdfs:subClassOf mmoon:Morph ;
           mmoon:definition """In a word-form: The stem is the morph to which inflectional marking applies. It is the morphological representative of the lexeme in a given word-form and is specified for part of speech.

In a derived word: The stem is the morphological representative of the lexical basis from which it is derived.

